### Track: Safety Hardening

M7 — Circuit Breaker for External Service Calls
Status: DONE
Completed: 2026-04-11
Notes: Addresses F-05. Depends on M0-M3.
Deliverables:
  - CircuitOpenError added to libs/contracts/errors.py (subclass of ExternalServiceError)
  - CircuitBreaker: thread-safe state machine (CLOSED/OPEN/HALF_OPEN)
    - Configurable thresholds (failure_threshold, recovery_timeout_s, half_open_max_calls)
    - Optional Redis-backed state persistence with graceful fallback
    - Error classification: TransientError/ExternalServiceError counted, AuthError/NotFoundError pass-through
    - Metrics: trip_count, recovery_count, current_state, failure_count
  - ResilientBrokerAdapter: decorator wrapping any BrokerAdapterInterface
    - Trading methods go through circuit breaker, lifecycle methods bypass
    - Diagnostics merge inner adapter + circuit breaker metrics
  - 32 circuit breaker unit tests + 24 resilient adapter unit tests (all passing)
  - §0 compliance verified, lint/format clean

