### Track: Operational Maturity

M11 — Graceful Shutdown and Startup Recovery
Status: DONE
Completed: 2026-04-11
Notes: Addresses F-11. Depends on M2 (persisted state), M4 (adapter lifecycle).
Deliverables:
  - DrainMiddleware: ASGI middleware for graceful request draining
    - Atomic in-flight request counter (_AtomicCounter, Lock-protected)
    - stop_accepting() → 503 for new requests (Retry-After: 5)
    - Health endpoint (/health) exempt from drain (load balancer probes)
    - wait_for_drain(timeout_s) blocks until count=0 or timeout
    - resume_accepting() for testing/cancellation
    - Thread-safe: concurrent increment/decrement verified
  - GracefulLifecycleManager: orchestrates shutdown and startup recovery
    - Shutdown: drain → reconcile → deregister_all → dispose engine
    - Startup: reconcile registered deployments, log discrepancies
    - Partial failure tolerance: individual recon/adapter errors caught and logged
    - SQLite in-memory dispose skip (preserves test data)
    - Configurable drain timeout via DRAIN_TIMEOUT_S env var (default 30s)
  - main.py lifespan enhanced:
    - Module-level _drain_middleware shared between lifespan and middleware stack
    - BrokerAdapterRegistry and GracefulLifecycleManager created in lifespan
    - app.state.broker_registry, lifecycle_manager, drain exposed for route access
    - Shutdown delegates to lifecycle_manager.shutdown()
    - Startup runs lifecycle_manager.startup_reconciliation()
    - DrainMiddleware registered as outermost middleware (before CorrelationID)
  - 12 drain middleware unit tests (all passing)
  - 15 lifecycle manager unit tests (all passing)
  - 2406 tests passing, 14 pre-existing failures (M12/M13), coverage 84.78%
  - §0 compliance verified, lint/format clean

